The paper discusses the organization and management of resources in smart environments, which involves various computing technologies such as cloud computing, fog computing, and IoT. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses ontology and taxonomy, which are related to knowledge representation and information retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the classification and categorization of resources, which could be related to Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the architecture of smart environments, which could be related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
